http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/mumbai/news/One-held-for-duping-people-of-Rs-1.7-lakh/article13978771.ece

One person has been arrested for allegedly duping at least 37 people of around Rs 1.72 lakh by promising lucrative returns while claiming to invest the money in a ‘government scheme’, police said on Saturday.The accused and his accomplice wooed people by promising huge returns on their investment in a ‘government scheme’, inspector M D Suryavanshi of Bazarpeth police station said.Following this, the people, mostly senior citizens, invested money into the scheme. One of the accused, Nanoo alias Dyaneshwar Moreshwar Ambre (48), a street-food seller, was arrested, Suryavanshi said.